# Carousel Background Images

This directory contains the background images for the homepage carousel slideshow.

## Image Specifications

- **Recommended Size**: 1920x1080 pixels (or higher resolution with 16:9 aspect ratio)
- **Format**: JPG, PNG, or WebP
- **File Size**: Optimize images for web (recommended < 500KB per image)
- **Number of Images**: Currently configured for 4 slides, but can be adjusted

## Current Carousel Slides

The carousel currently uses placeholder images. When you add your own images, you can use filenames like:
1. slide1.jpg - Epic 3D Environments
2. slide2.jpg - Character Design
3. slide3.jpg - Vehicle Assets
4. slide4.jpg - Weapon Models

(Or use any descriptive filenames you prefer)

## How to Add or Update Images

1. **Upload Images**: Place your images in this directory (`images/carousel/`)
2. **Name Your Images**: Use descriptive names (e.g., `slide1.jpg`, `slide2.jpg`, etc.)
3. **Update HTML**: Edit `index.html` and update the background image URLs in the hero section
   - Search for the `hero-slideshow` class or look for `.hero-slide` elements
   - Change `url('...')` to point to your new images
   - Example: `style="background-image: url('images/carousel/slide1.jpg')"`

## Example

```html
<div class="hero-slide active" style="background-image: url('images/carousel/slide1.jpg')"></div>
<div class="hero-slide" style="background-image: url('images/carousel/slide2.jpg')"></div>
<div class="hero-slide" style="background-image: url('images/carousel/slide3.jpg')"></div>
<div class="hero-slide" style="background-image: url('images/carousel/slide4.jpg')"></div>
```

## Tips

- Use high-quality images that represent your 3D artwork
- Ensure images have good contrast so the hero text remains readable
- Consider the dark overlay applied by CSS when choosing images
- Test the carousel on different screen sizes to ensure images look good on mobile devices
